title: GHS Boys Soccer: Galesburg 4th at Jacksonville
text: Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:15 PM Updated at 10:15 PM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:15 PM JACKSONVILLE â€” The Galesburg High School boys soccer team finished fourth out of eight teams at the Jacksonville Tournament on Friday and Saturday. The Silver Streaks opened their play with a 3-1 win over Jacksonville Red. Galesburg lost its second match falling to Rochester 4-3 on a penalty kick. The Streaks dropped the third-place match 1-0 to Jacksonville White 1-0. Normal U-High won the tournament with a 3-0 win over Rochester in the championship match. Bloomington won the consolation bracket with a 3-1 win over Champaign Centennial. The Register-Mail
